item.title: Jane add a quote by A. Sachs
item.description: "Death is more universal than life; everyone dies but not everyone lives." -- A. Sachs

item.title: Jane add a quote by Dick Innes
item.description: "One of my greatest strengths is to admit my weaknesses." -- Dick Innes

item.title: Jane add a quote by Denis Waitley
item.description: "It's not what you are that holds you back, it's what you think you are not." -- Denis Waitley

item.title: Jane add a quote by John Lennon
item.description: "There are two basic motivating forces: fear and love. When we are afraid, we pull back from life. When we are in love, we open to all that life has to offer with passion, excitement, and acceptance. We need to learn to love ourselves first, in all our glory and our imperfections. If we cannot love ourselves, we cannot fully open to our ability to love others or our potential to create. Evolution and all hopes for a better world rest in the fearlessness and open-hearted vision of people who embrace life." -- John Lennon

item.title: Jane add a quote by Wayne Dyer
item.description: "All blame is a waste of time. No matter how much fault you find with another, and regardless of how much you blame him, it will not change you. The only thing blame does is to keep the focus off you when you are looking for external reasons to explain your unhappiness or frustration. You may succeed in making another feel guilty about something by blaming him, but you won't succeed in changing whatever it is about you that is making you unhappy. " -- Wayne Dyer

item.title: Jane add a quote by Albert Einstein
item.description: "Anyone who has never made a mistake has never tried anything new." -- Albert Einstein

item.title: Jane add a quote by Wayne Dyer
item.description: "The more you see yourself as what you'd like to become, and act as if what you want is already there, the more you'll activate those dormant forces that will collaborate to transform your dream into your reality." -- Wayne Dyer

item.title: Jane add a quote by Pierre Teilhard de Chardin
item.description: "We are not human beings having a spiritual experience. We are spiritual beings having a human experience." -- Pierre Teilhard de Chardin
